# External scientific data: retain instructions, never commit payloads.
data/*
!data/.gitkeep
!data/README.md
!data/fetch_de_stats.sh

# Removed analysis surfaces must not reappear as local caches.
analysis_cache/
outputs/

# Cross-dataset effect-matrix caches (large, local, and required by exact byte identity;
# see data/README.md for reconstruction and durable-availability boundaries). Never commit.
slice/

# Exploratory baseline-ladder scratch is not claim-bearing until it has a checked-in,
# hash-bound runner and frozen configuration.
analysis/*

# Python and environments.
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.pytest_cache/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
.venv/
.env

# Generated/editor/OS debris.
*.log
.DS_Store

# Local agent operating manuals.
AGENTS.md
CLAUDE.md
.claude/

# Regenerated outputs under results/. A blanket `results/` rule used to live here,
# which silently swallowed every new file written into the directory -- including
# claim-bearing evidence that then never reached a clone. Ignore only what a script
# rewrites; the canonical frozen artifacts in results/ are tracked and hash-pinned
# via MANIFEST_PATHS in scripts/validate_findings.py.
/results/emergence_certificate_reproduced.csv
/results/certificate_dossier.json
/results/screenloop_campaign.json

# Root-level scratch / proof-of-concept outputs (root-anchored so the committed
# substrates combicone_substrate.npz / carpool_substrate.npz and the canonical
# docs/figures/ copies are never matched). Not claim-bearing.
/_view_*.png
/*_groundtruth.npz
/screenloop_poc.*
/screenloop_validation_*.json
# scripts/synth_triple_screen.py writes this CWD-relative, i.e. into the repo root;
# /*_groundtruth.npz does not match it.
/synth_triple_screen.npz
# Root-level build/scratch outputs whose canonical, tracked counterparts live in
# subdirectories. NOTE: /main.pdf and /certificate_dossier.json are NOT byte-identical
# to manuscript/main.pdf and results/certificate_dossier.json — they are stale/divergent
# root-level regenerations, ignored so they don't shadow the canonical copies (not
# throwaway duplicates; inspect before deleting). The /fig_screenloop_* root copies WERE
# byte-identical to docs/figures/ and have been removed.
/main.pdf
/certificate_dossier.json
/fig_screenloop_*.png
/fig_screenloop_*.pdf

# Manuscript held back from the public repo until it is ready (user decision,
# 2026-07-20 — "more work can be done"). The whole directory is ignored so no new
# manuscript files are staged. NOTE: the manuscript is ALSO already tracked and already
# on origin/main, so this ignore does not by itself remove it from the public repo —
# that requires `git rm -r --cached manuscript/` (keeps the files on disk) followed by a
# commit and a push to main. Files stay on disk for continued work either way.
manuscript/

# Generated API documentation. site/index.html is hand-authored and tracked;
# everything under site/api/ and site/figures/ is regenerated by build_docs.sh.
site/api/
site/figures/
